The paper presents a planning algorithm for collaborative multiagent dynamical systems, which involves distributed computation and coordination between agents. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI), multiagent systems (cs.MA), robotics (cs.RO), and control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of linear programming and message passing algorithms, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG).
